2.Canvisualperceptiongroundlanguageorvice versa?
Itisoftenheldthatlinguisticmeaningiscloselyrelatedtoperceptual space,inparticulartovisualspace.11InGestaltpsychology,perception isguided by universalcategorization principles,so-calledGestalt principles.TheseprinciplesareBrstandforemostnon-linguistic,but language aids the perceiveras a constructive device in ascribing meaningtoperceptualGestalts.Severallinguistshavepickedupona similarview,andhaveattemptedtodetectprinciplessharedbyvisual perceptionandlinguisticmeaning.Beforeweturntotheseaccounts, onecannoticeatleasttwogeneralsimiliaritiesbetweenthetwo.First, bothlanguageandvisionareateverygivenmomentincompleteand opentofurtherexploration.Thereisneveramomentwhenthefull potentialofperceptionandlanguageisexhausted,buttherealways remainsthepossibilitytogooninquiring,asisproposedintheoriesof fuzzyboundaries12aswellasWittgenstein’s13familyresemblancesand languagegames.
